President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed November 21-27, 2021, as National Family Week in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the importance of spending time with family and emphasizes the need to support and invest in American families. President Biden highlights the challenges faced by families during the COVID-19 pandemic, such as job losses and food insecurity. He emphasizes the actions taken by his administration, including the American Rescue Plan, which provided cash assistance, supported schools, and expanded the Child Tax Credit. The Build Back Better Act and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act are also mentioned as measures to further strengthen and support families. These acts include investments in preschool, child care, healthcare, and a tax cut for families with children. President Biden expresses his commitment to establishing a paid family and medical leave program. The proclamation calls for observing National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor and support families.